---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Neck Pain"
	heroSubtitle="Neck pain is increasingly common — especially with long hours at desks, laptops and phones."
	breadcrumb="Neck Pain"
	seoTitle="Neck Pain Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert neck pain treatment in Clapham, London. We combine hands-on therapy with movement-based rehab to reduce pain, ease stiffness and restore comfortable movement."
	intro={[
		"At Balance Performance Physiotherapy, we look at what's really driving your symptoms. Whether it's posture, injury or movement-related, we'll help you reduce pain and get your neck moving comfortably again.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get your neck"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsList={[
		"Ongoing stiffness or difficulty turning your head",
		"Headaches starting from the base of the skull",
		"Pain, tingling or numbness into the shoulder or arm",
		"Symptoms following a knock or whiplash injury",
		"Tension through the neck, shoulders or upper back",
		"Pain that spreads into the jaw or between the shoulder blades",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="neck pain"
	treatmentIntro="We combine hands-on treatment with movement-based rehab to get the best results. Treatment may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve movement and control",
		"Manual therapy to reduce stiffness and pain",
		"Targeted exercises to build strength and support",
		"Posture and workstation advice to reduce strain",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Desk-based professionals dealing with postural strain or \"tech neck\"",
		"Active individuals and athletes managing injury or overload",
		"Whiplash and trauma recovery patients",
		"People with recurring headaches linked to the neck",
		"Seniors looking to maintain mobility and reduce stiffness",
		"Long-term back pain sufferers looking for a clear plan forward",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Why does neck pain cause headaches?", a: "Tension or stiffness in the upper neck can refer pain up into the head, often causing headaches." },
		{ q: "Do I need a scan?", a: "Usually not. We can assess your neck thoroughly in clinic and refer if needed." },
		{ q: "Can osteopathy help?", a: "Yes — particularly for stiffness, tension and joint-related neck pain." },
		{ q: "What is \"tech neck\"?", a: "It's strain caused by looking down at screens for long periods, which we can help correct." },
		{ q: "Are clicking or cracking sounds normal?", a: "Occasional clicking is common. If it's painful or linked with other symptoms, it's worth assessing." },
		{ q: "Will I get exercises to do at work?", a: "Yes — we'll give you simple movements you can fit into your day." },
	]}
/>
